
3-Two
3-Data Governance Under IT: A Look at the Downside
A chief data officer, who’s organization has placed DG governance under IT, expresses his critical outlook for this reporting hierarchy. In his opinion, DG and data management are often eclipsed by the specter of IT agenda and are relegated to a second or third-tier priority in the CIO. “The result is that the CIO drives the data management and governance agenda over the needs of the business who are competing for limited time and resources to advance their data projects,” the peer adds. Focusing on the positive aspect of the approach, the peer states, “At same time, this approach does allow for closer collaboration between IT and data than otherwise might be the case.”
